title: UVM books spot in America East tournament
text:
UVM books spot in America East tournament Free Press Sports Staff 9:39 a.m. EDT October 26, 2015 Buy Photo Vermont forward Nikki McFarland controls the ball ahead of a Maine defender during Thursday's women's soccer game at Virtue Field. (Photo: AUSTIN DANFORTH/FREE PRESS) Buy Photo CONNECT 4 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
VESTAL, N.Y. - Vermont scored twice in a span of 1 minute, 47 seconds of the second half to earn a 2-1 victory over Binghamton in women's soccer in the regular season finale on Sunday. 
Rylee Osgood and Nikki McFarland each had a goal for the Catamounts (7-7-1, 4-3-1), who qualified for the America East Conference tournament with the win. Ally Ramos had seven saves. 
The Catamounts earned the No. 3 seed and will play host to Maryland-Baltimore County at Virtue Field on Thursday at 7 p.m. 
Katherine Corcoran scored for Binghamton (3-12-2, 2-5-1) and Katie Hatziyianis made five saves. 
FIELD HOCKEY 
•Vermont 4, UMass Lowell 1: Anne-Marie Farmer had two goals to lead Vermont to a win over host UMass-Lowell as the Catamounts posted a season-high four tallies. 
Lauren Tucker and Landon Warren also scored for the Catamounts (4-12, 2-5) and Lena Benwood stopped four saves. 
The Riverhawks (5-12, 0-7) got a goal from Torrie Huk and Kelsey Frederico stopped five shots. 
WOMEN'S ICE HOCKEY 
•Boston University 5, Vermont 2: Maddie Elia scored two goals and added an assist to lead No. 10 Boston University to a win over visiting Vermont. 
Victoria Bach, Sarah Steele and Rebecca Russo each chipped in with a goal for the Terriers (4-4, 3-1) and Erin O'Neil had 23 saves to earn the win. 
Dayna Colang and Rachael Ade scored for the Catamounts (1-7, 1-1) and Molly Depew stopped 34 shots. Read or Share this story: http://bfpne.ws/1N2hNAi TOP VIDEOS
